1
00:00:10,051 --> 00:00:13,847
A NETFLIX ORIGINAL SERIES

2
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:03,354
THIS DRAMA IS PURELY FICTIONAL
AND IS NOT ASSOCIATED WITH

3
00:01:03,438 --> 00:01:05,982
ACTUAL PEOPLE, PARTIES, LOCATIONS,
CORPORATIONS OR INCIDENTS

4
00:01:29,839 --> 00:01:31,132
One ice flake, please.

5
00:01:36,012 --> 00:01:38,431
Here is your ice flake.

6
00:01:47,398 --> 00:01:48,858
-It's good.
-Is it?

7
00:01:49,734 --> 00:01:51,069
Try some, Tae-jun.

8
00:01:55,490 --> 00:01:56,783
It is good.

9
00:01:57,408 --> 00:02:00,578
We had ice flakes on our first date too.

10
00:02:00,662 --> 00:02:03,623
-Do you remember?
-Yes, you were wearing a sky blue blouse.

11
00:02:05,917 --> 00:02:08,294
You dropped condensed milk on it

12
00:02:08,378 --> 00:02:12,298
-because you were nervous to be with me.
-My gosh.

13
00:02:13,091 --> 00:02:14,968
-What are you saying?
-Don't you remember?

14
00:02:15,051 --> 00:02:17,095
You got so nervous and spilled everything.

15
00:02:17,178 --> 00:02:19,264
-You're completely mistaken.
-No, I'm not.

16
00:02:19,347 --> 00:02:20,557
You were the nervous one.

17
00:02:20,807 --> 00:02:23,393
You were so nervous to see me
that you kept on gulping.

18
00:02:24,435 --> 00:02:25,770
Goodness.

19
00:02:26,813 --> 00:02:27,981
Back then,

20
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:32,402
it was great how we could just hang out
without having to worry.

21
00:02:33,945 --> 00:02:36,239
-What about now?
-Now?

22
00:02:36,322 --> 00:02:37,365
It's still fun.

23
00:02:38,491 --> 00:02:39,617
It's not that bad.

24
00:02:46,666 --> 00:02:48,751
Why are you shaking?

25
00:02:50,628 --> 00:02:52,797
Look at this. You're shaking.

26
00:02:52,881 --> 00:02:54,340
Do you still like me that much?

27
00:02:56,843 --> 00:03:00,388
Assemblywoman Jeong Eun-hui was appointed
as Daehan Party's new spokesperson.

28
00:03:00,471 --> 00:03:02,348
She shared her determination to report

29
00:03:02,432 --> 00:03:05,602
the opinions of her party to the people
with honesty before anything.

30
00:03:06,227 --> 00:03:09,063
She also said that she will do her best
as the spokesperson

31
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:11,649
-for the party supported by people.
-Are you okay?

32
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,944
-She will tune into people's opinions
-It is what it is.

33
00:03:15,028 --> 00:03:16,446
and liaise more with the press.

34
00:03:17,363 --> 00:03:19,115
At least you saved my bill.

35
00:03:21,117 --> 00:03:22,452
It's all for the better.

36
00:03:22,535 --> 00:03:24,537
There was too much to do
as a spokesperson.

37
00:03:26,372 --> 00:03:27,874
I'll focus on Jungil-gu now.

38
00:03:31,586 --> 00:03:33,671
Is the preparation
for the hearing going well?

39
00:03:35,006 --> 00:03:37,008
Yes, so far.

40
00:03:38,843 --> 00:03:40,094
Once the hearing begins,

41
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:44,182
every single thing that Mr. Song has done
will be brought up.

42
00:03:44,265 --> 00:03:45,558
Even Samil Association.

43
00:03:47,894 --> 00:03:48,811
You're right.

44
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:51,731
Samil Association might end up
dragging you down.

45
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:54,067
I know.

46
00:03:56,986 --> 00:03:58,655
I'm aware of that, so don't worry.

47
00:04:11,167 --> 00:04:13,503
We've raced to this day restlessly,

48
00:04:14,337 --> 00:04:15,922
but we still have

49
00:04:17,340 --> 00:04:18,716
a long way to go.

50
00:04:22,428 --> 00:04:25,723
Everyone is running toward
their own light.

51
00:04:30,645 --> 00:04:31,562
But...

52
00:04:32,522 --> 00:04:35,316
when you get closer to the light,
it becomes difficult to see.

53
00:04:37,402 --> 00:04:40,238
And you won't even be able to see
the darkness under your feet.

54
00:05:01,968 --> 00:05:05,013
EPISODE 6

55
00:05:06,889 --> 00:05:09,434
The Minister of Justice nominee
will be undergoing

56
00:05:09,517 --> 00:05:11,811
a confirmation hearing
by the National Assembly

57
00:05:11,894 --> 00:05:13,229
in the coming week.

58
00:05:13,896 --> 00:05:16,190
The ruling party is mostly welcoming

59
00:05:16,316 --> 00:05:19,944
the nomination of Mr. Song, the current
floor leader of the Daehan Party,

60
00:05:20,528 --> 00:05:23,323
but we expect to see
a harsh attack from the opposition party.

61
00:05:24,365 --> 00:05:26,117
A harsh attack, my ass.

62
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:27,577
They're assemblymen too.

63
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:30,538
There's no need to stop an assemblyman
from becoming a minister.

64
00:05:30,621 --> 00:05:33,333
They wouldn't stop me
even if they didn't want to.

65
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,877
There will be reporters there.

66
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:37,837
I put together a simple greeting.

67
00:05:38,463 --> 00:05:40,840
I'll hold a press conference
to announce your policy.

68
00:05:40,923 --> 00:05:42,050
Go ahead.

69
00:05:43,134 --> 00:05:45,928
Oh, and I'm meeting Lee Chang-jin later.

70
00:05:46,012 --> 00:05:47,722
He wants to buy me food to celebrate.

71
00:05:48,264 --> 00:05:49,932
-Come with me.
-Yes, sir.

72
00:05:54,187 --> 00:05:56,314
The weather is very nice today.

73
00:06:02,528 --> 00:06:03,780
What's your name again?

74
00:06:04,572 --> 00:06:05,782
It's Kim Myeong-su.

75
00:06:06,324 --> 00:06:08,159
Kim Myeong-su...

76
00:06:08,242 --> 00:06:09,869
Where did it go?

77
00:06:10,328 --> 00:06:11,621
I remember leaving it here.

78
00:06:12,497 --> 00:06:15,333
One second, please. Do-gyeong?

79
00:06:15,416 --> 00:06:17,502
Is he still asleep?

80
00:06:17,585 --> 00:06:19,212
How much did he drink yesterday?

81
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:26,761
Do-gyeong! Wake up.

82
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:29,305
Goodness, wake up!

83
00:06:29,889 --> 00:06:32,934
-What?
-Did you organize last year's suits?

84
00:06:34,185 --> 00:06:35,812
What? Suits?

85
00:06:38,981 --> 00:06:41,651
-A customer came by, but I can't find it.
-My gosh.

86
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:46,114
Why did he suddenly come to pick it up?

87
00:06:46,197 --> 00:06:49,033
He had forgotten about it,
but remembered it before moving.

88
00:06:49,117 --> 00:06:51,369
-Have you seen it?
-How would I know?

89
00:06:51,452 --> 00:06:52,620
I'll try looking for it.

90
00:06:52,703 --> 00:06:56,207
Go tell him that
we'll find it and send it to him.

91
00:06:56,290 --> 00:06:59,585
Okay, we should do that.
He's busy packing for his move.

92
00:07:01,295 --> 00:07:02,463
Do-gyeong.

93
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:04,090
Yes, what?

94
00:07:04,173 --> 00:07:05,466
Studying must be stressful.

95
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:08,219
But still, don't drink too much.

96
00:07:08,302 --> 00:07:10,763
You need to maintain your condition.
Your exam is soon.

97
00:07:10,847 --> 00:07:13,307
-Keep it up!
-Okay, fine.

98
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:25,111
I'm late.

99
00:07:34,871 --> 00:07:37,582
I'm sorry.
I'm sure we'll be able to find...

100
00:07:37,665 --> 00:07:39,709
-Where are you going?
-To study.

101
00:07:39,792 --> 00:07:42,128
We'll have your suit cleaned
and send it over.

102
00:07:42,211 --> 00:07:43,921
-Don't worry.
-What about breakfast?

103
00:07:44,005 --> 00:07:44,881
I'll eat there.

104
00:07:51,012 --> 00:07:52,180
I'm sorry.

105
00:08:08,029 --> 00:08:09,322
What brings you here?

106
00:08:10,031 --> 00:08:11,949
I'm an intern at Mr. Song's office,

107
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:13,367
but I forgot my pass.

108
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:15,995
-Are you sure you work here?
-Yes.

109
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:18,080
-What about your ID?
-My ID?

110
00:08:18,831 --> 00:08:20,374
-Hello.
-Hello.

111
00:08:20,458 --> 00:08:22,168
He is our intern.

112
00:08:24,629 --> 00:08:25,630
Thank you.

113
00:08:26,547 --> 00:08:27,840
-Thank you.
-Access granted.

114
00:08:37,099 --> 00:08:40,728
Why did you quit working as a reporter
to do this job?

115
00:08:44,023 --> 00:08:45,650
Your articles looked great.

116
00:08:46,442 --> 00:08:50,279
I didn't want to write articles anymore.

117
00:08:52,490 --> 00:08:54,200
The man you saw at the hospital,

118
00:08:54,283 --> 00:08:55,451
Mr. Shin Jae-gyeong.

119
00:08:56,786 --> 00:08:58,746
He ended up like that
because of my article.

120
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:12,843
-Hello.
-Good morning.

121
00:09:15,846 --> 00:09:16,847
You're here.

122
00:09:16,931 --> 00:09:19,809
What? You're all fine?

123
00:09:21,435 --> 00:09:22,687
Gosh, my stomach hurts.

124
00:09:23,145 --> 00:09:24,272
Ms. No.

125
00:09:30,194 --> 00:09:33,406
Ms. No, can you get me some coffee?
With three spoons of sugar.

126
00:09:35,241 --> 00:09:36,367
Sure.

127
00:09:38,244 --> 00:09:40,204
This is Yun Hye-won of Mr. Song's office.

128
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:44,375
The nominee's pre-questionnaire
and documents for the hearing?

129
00:09:45,084 --> 00:09:47,003
Yes, we'll fill them out and turn them in.

130
00:09:47,086 --> 00:09:48,462
Yes, all right.

131
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:52,633
The pre-questionnaires from assemblymen
will start coming in soon.

132
00:09:53,926 --> 00:09:55,678
Why can't we ever catch a break?

133
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:03,019
What a crowd.

134
00:10:03,686 --> 00:10:07,023
I guess it's great to have
a lot of people here on a day like this.

135
00:10:14,655 --> 00:10:15,740
There he is.

136
00:10:20,661 --> 00:10:22,413
Congratulations on your nomination.

137
00:10:22,496 --> 00:10:24,248
Please tell us how you feel.

138
00:10:24,332 --> 00:10:27,877
This is an important position, so I am
burdened with a sense of responsibility.

139
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:30,171
I'll listen closely to people's opinions

140
00:10:30,254 --> 00:10:33,215
and communicate closely
with the Blue House.

141
00:10:33,299 --> 00:10:35,718
What is your position
on the prosecution reformation?

142
00:10:35,801 --> 00:10:37,094
Prosecution reformation is

143
00:10:37,178 --> 00:10:40,765
something that we cannot avoid
to protect the democracy

144
00:10:40,848 --> 00:10:42,600
and constitutionalism of our nation.

145
00:10:42,683 --> 00:10:46,062
I will continue to contemplate on
what the prosecution should look like,

146
00:10:46,145 --> 00:10:48,189
receive opinions from various circles,

147
00:10:48,272 --> 00:10:51,192
and approach this matter with discretion.

148
00:10:51,275 --> 00:10:53,486
Many think that it'd be hard
to proceed with it

149
00:10:53,569 --> 00:10:56,322
if the Minister of Justice was
formerly with the prosecution.

150
00:10:56,405 --> 00:10:59,241
I may have been
with the prosecution in the past, but...

151
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:00,493
You're still here?

152
00:11:01,577 --> 00:11:03,954
I should congratulate Mr. Song
before I leave.

153
00:11:04,038 --> 00:11:06,248
I'd like to express
my determination for it.

154
00:11:06,332 --> 00:11:08,918
I would like all of your support
rather than concerns.

155
00:11:09,001 --> 00:11:11,212
Thank you. I look forward to your support.

156
00:11:11,295 --> 00:11:12,171
Thank you.

157
00:11:19,428 --> 00:11:20,638
Prosecution reformation is

158
00:11:20,888 --> 00:11:24,684
something that we cannot avoid to protect
the democracy and constitutionalism

159
00:11:25,017 --> 00:11:26,268
of our nation.

160
00:11:26,352 --> 00:11:28,354
Mr. Song met with Lee Sang-guk last night,

161
00:11:28,437 --> 00:11:30,481
the chairperson
of the Judiciary Committee.

162
00:11:31,649 --> 00:11:35,528
So Mr. Song wants to pull out
after getting what he needs.

163
00:11:35,611 --> 00:11:39,615
I'm sure Ms. Kang was the one
that persuaded Chairperson Lee.

164
00:11:39,699 --> 00:11:41,158
Will you let her go on?

165
00:11:41,242 --> 00:11:43,994
A women's organization will award her
because of that bill.

166
00:11:44,078 --> 00:11:45,996
-Leave her be.
-Really?

167
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:48,416
If you don't do anything,
it'll be hard for you

168
00:11:48,499 --> 00:11:50,042
to be appointed floor leader.

169
00:11:50,126 --> 00:11:51,293
Hey.

170
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:54,463
That's only if Mr. Song
passes the confirmation hearing.

171
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:58,217
The Judiciary Committee heads the hearing
for the Minister of Justice.

172
00:11:58,300 --> 00:12:01,303
If you step in and do something,
it'll cause a lot of problems.

173
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:04,473
It won't be me.
Kang Seon-yeong will do it.

174
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:05,975
-What?
-Ms. Kang?

175
00:12:06,058 --> 00:12:07,143
Yes.

176
00:12:07,935 --> 00:12:10,229
Let her enjoy her victory until then.

177
00:12:13,065 --> 00:12:15,985
This person has contributed greatly
to improving women's rights

178
00:12:16,068 --> 00:12:20,239
as a proud woman of our society.
Therefore, we give you this award.

179
00:12:24,368 --> 00:12:25,453
Congratulations.

180
00:12:26,537 --> 00:12:28,289
JUNGIL-GU WOMEN'S ORGANIZATION
AWARDS CEREMONY

181
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:35,546
Thank you.

182
00:12:36,297 --> 00:12:39,216
Here's the seating chart
of the members of the hearing committee.

183
00:12:39,383 --> 00:12:41,093
Jo Nam-hyeon, Baek Seung-hwan,

184
00:12:41,177 --> 00:12:43,345
and Kim Sang-jun,
who were on Mr. Jo's side,

185
00:12:43,429 --> 00:12:44,805
will not cause any trouble.

186
00:12:44,889 --> 00:12:47,141
They probably know
that the situation has changed.

187
00:12:47,224 --> 00:12:49,560
-What about the opposition party?
-It is fine,

188
00:12:49,643 --> 00:12:51,812
but Mr. Jang is still on Mr. Jo's side.

189
00:12:51,896 --> 00:12:55,191
Jang Yong-gi? He made a scene
during the last audit, didn't he?

190
00:12:56,025 --> 00:12:57,359
-Mr. Song!
-Quiet!

191
00:12:57,443 --> 00:13:01,113
If you do not bring Mr. Lee as a witness,
you cannot continue with the inspection!

192
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:03,073
But do not worry too much.

193
00:13:03,157 --> 00:13:06,160
Mr. Jang is involved in a lawsuit
for driving under the influence.

194
00:13:06,243 --> 00:13:09,663
-I could get him for sure.
-Okay, then.

195
00:13:09,747 --> 00:13:12,416
What about Mun Sang-hyeon
of the Kookmin Party?

196
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:13,709
Mun Sang-hyeon?

197
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:16,879
-Is it because Mr. Lee has a special
-Enough!

198
00:13:17,004 --> 00:13:19,882
-relationship with Mr. Song?
-The witness list was finalized.

199
00:13:19,965 --> 00:13:24,512
Well, he is like a leech,
sucking on blood here and there.

200
00:13:25,638 --> 00:13:29,558
He might be trouble
if we don't give him anything.

201
00:13:29,642 --> 00:13:30,935
Where is his district?

202
00:13:32,311 --> 00:13:33,813
It's Jungil-gu.

203
00:13:35,731 --> 00:13:36,899
Jungil-gu?

204
00:13:36,982 --> 00:13:39,693
Ms. Kang has been
working hard in the area.

205
00:13:46,242 --> 00:13:47,993
SEATING CHART FOR
SONG HUI-SEOP'S HEARING

206
00:13:49,787 --> 00:13:52,957
Ms. Kang stepped down
as the spokesperson of her party.

207
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:55,292
If she is more pressured,
she may take action.

208
00:13:55,376 --> 00:13:57,002
That's why I brought her up.

209
00:13:57,086 --> 00:14:00,381
We don't know what she will do,
so we should do something about her now.

210
00:14:00,464 --> 00:14:02,800
Mr. Song, it looked like
Mr. Mun considered

211
00:14:02,883 --> 00:14:05,636
leaving his party
because of next year's nomination.

212
00:14:05,719 --> 00:14:09,056
If he comes to our party now,
don't you think he could be of support?

213
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:23,779
-Go and sound him out.
-Yes, sir.

214
00:14:38,419 --> 00:14:39,461
Won-sik.

215
00:14:41,547 --> 00:14:42,423
A word, please.

216
00:14:42,506 --> 00:14:45,134
Why do you want to go somewhere else?
Talk to me here.

217
00:14:49,013 --> 00:14:52,349
He has so many secrets.

218
00:14:53,434 --> 00:14:55,811
If Mr. Jang asks for me to come,
I have no choice.

219
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:56,854
Take this.

220
00:15:00,774 --> 00:15:01,734
Goodbye.

221
00:15:04,028 --> 00:15:06,363
What's going on? Do you know anything?

222
00:15:07,281 --> 00:15:08,407
No.

223
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:12,036
It feels like walking on thin ice.

224
00:15:13,037 --> 00:15:14,330
Congratulations, Ms. Kang.

225
00:15:15,039 --> 00:15:17,833
Thank you. It's all thanks to you.

226
00:15:17,917 --> 00:15:20,669
Of course.
Do not forget all of my hard work.

227
00:15:20,753 --> 00:15:21,754
I won't.

228
00:15:22,755 --> 00:15:25,382
Didn't you drink a lot yesterday?
Are you okay?

229
00:15:26,050 --> 00:15:28,135
I'll go for some hangover soup
when I get back.

230
00:15:30,679 --> 00:15:32,848
Have you heard from the Jungil-gu mayor
yet?

231
00:15:32,932 --> 00:15:36,518
No. He wants to be a part
of the lone-parent support project,

232
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:39,647
but he seems to be concerned
about what Mr. Jo would think.

233
00:15:48,530 --> 00:15:51,533
I told you to stay still
if you want to keep what you have.

234
00:15:52,743 --> 00:15:55,537
You should stay still
if you want anything at all.

235
00:15:57,247 --> 00:15:59,792
-What?
-How was the movie last night?

236
00:15:59,875 --> 00:16:01,585
It was pretty boring for me.

237
00:16:04,004 --> 00:16:05,631
What are you talking about?

238
00:16:08,634 --> 00:16:11,261
The head chief of staff
with an incumbent assemblywoman.

239
00:16:11,845 --> 00:16:14,431
Right? Getting it on.

240
00:16:14,515 --> 00:16:17,309
You must have had a wild night.
You look worn out.

241
00:16:20,437 --> 00:16:22,481
What do you think Mr. Song will say

242
00:16:22,564 --> 00:16:25,025
if he finds out about
your relationship with Ms. Kang?

243
00:16:25,901 --> 00:16:27,611
Leave the hearing to me from now on.

244
00:16:27,695 --> 00:16:30,698
Then settle the district's problem
and hand it over to me too.

245
00:16:31,281 --> 00:16:32,324
That's the only way

246
00:16:32,908 --> 00:16:35,077
you will keep my mouth shut.

247
00:16:45,629 --> 00:16:48,298
Mr. Jang, Mr. Song just left
to the restaurant.

248
00:16:50,175 --> 00:16:51,969
-Hye-won.
-Yes?

249
00:16:52,052 --> 00:16:53,721
Let's get rid of Oh Won-sik

250
00:16:53,804 --> 00:16:55,222
before Mr. Song's hearing.

251
